OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1774944309
OL,3,CMan who threatened petrol station
OL,4,Cworkers with imitation firearm jailed
OL,6,FA man from Sittingbourne who
OL,7,Fthreatened two petrol station workers
OL,8,Fwith an imitation firearm during a
OL,9,Frobbery has been jailed.
OL,11,FMichael Pollock entered the BP Service
OL,12,FStation on the London Road, in
OL,13,FBapchild, just before 9.30 pm on
OL,14,FSunday 12 October. He demanded that a
OL,15,Fmember of staff open the till, or he
OL,16,Fwould shoot them.
OL,18,FThe 35-year-old also threatened
OL,19,Fanother member of staff, repeatedly
OL,20,Fshouting at him while pointing his
OL,21,Fweapon.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/5
